mim.author: EAB/FJP/TA UABJOCL
mim.name: RsyncPtpBcOcPort
mim.description:
ECIM Transport PTP Port Model.
PTP port is used to communicate with other 1588 devices.

struct.name: PortDS
struct.description: This data set describe, the port properties.

structMember.name: announceInterval
structMember.description: Indicates the announce message interval in logarithm(base2).

structMember.name: announceReceiptTimeout
structMember.description: Indicates the number of announce message intervals, for which announce messages must be missing to change the state in the clock.

structMember.name: delayMechanism
structMember.description:
Indicates the delay mechanism used by the port.
Presently the only mechanism supported is E2E.

structMember.name: minDelayReqInterval
structMember.description: It indicates the minimum delay request interval expressed as logarith(base2).

structMember.name: minPdelayReqInterval
structMember.description: It indicates the minimum peer delay request interval expressed as logarithm(base2).

structMember.name: peerMeanPathDelay
structMember.description:
It indicates the peer mean path delay.
If the delay mechanism is end to end , the value is zero.

structMember.name: portClockIdentity
structMember.description: It indicates the identity of the local port.

structMember.name: portNumber
structMember.description: The value of the portNumber on a PTP node with a single PTP port shall be 1. The values of the port numbers for the N ports on a PTP node supporting N PTP ports shall be 1, 2, â€¦N. The all-zeros and all-ones portNumber values are reserved.

structMember.name: portState
structMember.description: It indicates the state of the local port.

structMember.name: syncInterval
structMember.description: It indicates the synchronization message interval expressed in the logarithm(base2).

enum.name: AdmState
enum.description: The administrative state of a resource.

enumMember.name: LOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively prohibited from performing services for its users.

enumMember.name: UNLOCKED
enumMember.description: The resource is administratively permitted to perform services for its users. This is independent of its inherent operability.

enumMember.name: SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: Use of the resource is administratively permitted to existing instances of use only. While the system remains in the shutting down state the manager may at any time cause the managed object to revert to the locked state.

enum.name: AvailStatus
enum.description: The availability status is used to qualify the operational state. It indicates why the operational state has changed its value.

enumMember.name: IN_TEST
enumMember.description: The resource is undergoing a test procedure. If the administrative state is locked or shutting down then normal users are precluded from using the resource.

enumMember.name: FAILED
enumMember.description: The resource has an internal fault that prevents it from operating.

enumMember.name: POWER_OFF
enumMember.description: The resource requires power to be applied and is not powered on.

enumMember.name: OFF_LINE
enumMember.description: The resource requires a routine operation to be performed. This routine operation is to place the resource online and make it available for use. The operation may be manual or automatic, or both. The operational state is disabled.

enumMember.name: OFF_DUTY
enumMember.description: The resource has been made inactive by an internal control process.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY
enumMember.description: The resource cannot operate because some other resource on which it depends is unavailable.

enumMember.name: DEGRADED
enumMember.description: The service available from the resource is degraded in some respect.

enumMember.name: NOT_INSTALLED
enumMember.description: The resource represented by the managed object is not present, or is incomplete.

enumMember.name: LOG_FULL
enumMember.description: This indicates a log full condition.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_LOCKED
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is locked. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency locked.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_FAILED
enumMember.description: The availability status of a resource that this resource depends on is failed or dependency failed.

enumMember.name: DEPENDENCY_SHUTTINGDOWN
enumMember.description: The administrative state of a resource that this resource depends on is shutting down. or the availability status of the other resource is dependency shutting down.

enum.name: DelayMechanism
enum.description:
Available delay mechanism modes.
The delay mechanism modes indicate the propagation delay measuring option used by the port in computing <meanPathDelay>.

enum.name: OperState
enum.description: The operational states of a resource.

enumMember.name: DISABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is totally inoperable.

enumMember.name: ENABLED
enumMember.description: The resource is partially or fully operable.

enum.name: PortState
enum.description: Available port states of a PTP port.

enum.name: PtpMulticastAddress
enum.description: Specifies which type of multicast address that shall be used.

enumMember.name: FORWARDABLE
enumMember.description: Forwardable multicast MAC address 01-1B-19-00-00-00.

enumMember.name: NON_FORWARDABLE
enumMember.description: Non-forwardable multicast MAC address 01-80-C2-00-00-0E.

enumMember.name: NO_FAULT
enumMember.description: No fault is detected.

enumMember.name: UNRESOLVED_SERVER_ADDRESS
enumMember.description: The server address cannot be resolved.

enumMember.name: NEGOTIATION_FAILED
enumMember.description: At any time during operation, the grandmaster cancels a previously granted unicast transmission agreement, or the grandmaster does not comply with the requested negotiation service.

enumMember.name: NEGOTIATION_NO_REPLY
enumMember.description: No reply from the grandmaster to the slave's Unicast Request.

class.name: PtpBcOcPort
class.description:
Represents PTP port to communicate with other 1588 devices.
Grandmaster ordinary clock can have more than one port. Slave-only ordinary clock can only have one port.

validationRules.rule: <schema xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"> <pattern> <rule> <assert test='not(((../@ptpProfile eq 1) or (../@ptpProfile eq 2) or (../@ptpProfile eq 5) or (../@ptpProfile eq 6)) and not(contains(@transportInterface, "EthernetPort=")))'> <value-of select="."/> If attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is IEEE_1588_J3, or G_8275_1, or IEEE_1588_TIME_DEFAULT, or IEEE_1588_TIME_SLOW, attribute transportInterface must refer to EthernetPort MO. </assert> <assert test='not(((../@ptpProfile eq 3) or (../@ptpProfile eq 4)) and not(contains(@transportInterface, "AddressIPv4=") or contains(@transportInterface, "AddressIPv6=")))'> <value-of select="."/> If attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is G_8265_1 or G_8275_2, attribute transportInterface must refer to AddressIPv4 MO or AddressIPv6 MO. </assert> <assert test='every $ti in @transportInterface satisfies every $gm in @associatedGrandmaster satisfies not(count(../../BoundaryOrdinaryClock/PtpBcOcPort[((../@ptpProfile eq 3) or (../@ptpProfile eq 4)) and ($ti eq @transportInterface) and ($gm eq @associatedGrandmaster)]) gt 1)'> <value-of select="."/> If attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is G_8265_1 or G_8275_2, two PtpBcOcPort MOs cannot have same combination of transportInterface and associatedGrandmaster. </assert> <assert test='not(((../@ptpProfile eq 3) or (../@ptpProfile eq 4)) and (@transportVlan))'> <value-of select="."/> If attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is G_8265_1 or G_8275_2, attribute transportVlan must be NIL. </assert> <assert test='every $tv in @transportVlan satisfies ($tv/@isTagged)'> <value-of select="."/> transportVlan cannot refer to VlanPort MO when its attribute isTagged as false. </assert> <assert test='(every $ti in @transportInterface satisfies every $id in ../@boundaryOrdinaryClockId satisfies not(count(../../BoundaryOrdinaryClock/PtpBcOcPort[($id eq ../@boundaryOrdinaryClockId) and ($ti eq @transportInterface) and not(@transportVlan)]) gt 1)) and (every $tv in @transportVlan satisfies every $ti in @transportInterface satisfies every $id in ../@boundaryOrdinaryClockId satisfies not(count(../../BoundaryOrdinaryClock/PtpBcOcPort[($tv eq @transportVlan) and ($id eq ../@boundaryOrdinaryClockId) and ($ti eq @transportInterface)]) gt 1))'> <value-of select="."/> When two PtpBcOcPort MOs refer to same EthernetPort MO, then their transportVlan attributes must have different values. One of them can be NIL, but not both. </assert> <assert test='every $tv in @transportVlan satisfies every $ti in @transportInterface satisfies ((contains($tv/@encapsulation, "EthernetPort=") and ($tv/@encapsulation eq $ti)) or (contains($tv/@encapsulation, "LagPort=") and (count($tv/@encapsulation/@encapsulation[. eq $ti]) gt 0))) '> <value-of select="."/> When attribute transportVlan is not NIL, it must refer to VlanPort MO, where VlanPort::encapsulation refers to same EthernetPort MO as attribute transportVlan, or VlanPort::encapsulation refers to LagPort MO, where one value in LagPort MO::encapsulation refers to same EthernetPort MO as attribute transportVlan. </assert> </rule> </pattern> </schema>

attribute.name: administrativeState
attribute.description: The administrative state.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: announceMessageInterval
attribute.description:
Announce message transmission interval expressed as logarithm of time in seconds (base of 2). Result indicates time in seconds between messages.
Example: If value is 4, message is sent every 16 seconds.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: associatedGrandmaster
attribute.description:
IP address or domain name of associated grandmaster according to G.8265.1 or G.8275.2.
PTP associated grandmaster and PTP slave must have same IP version.
attribute.dependencies: All ports created on slave-only ordinary clocks with ptpProfile G_8265_1 or G_8275_2 must have unique combination of IP address, associatedGrandmaster and transportInterface.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: asymmetryCompensation
attribute.description:
Assymetry compensation.
+/- sign specifies uplink delay relative to downlink. Attribute is not used in frequency profile. Attribute is applicable to slave port.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: availabilityStatus
attribute.description:
The availability status.
It contains details about operationalState.

attribute.name: cachedIpAddress
attribute.description: Cached IP address obtained from DNS for PTP frequency grandmaster.

attribute.name: dscp
attribute.description: DSCP value for PTP related IP packets.

attribute.name: durationField
attribute.description: Time that packet master transmitting requested Announce and Sync message rates and renewal of Announce and Sync before expiration.

attribute.name: localPriority
attribute.description:
Local priority used if alternate BMCA is activated.
Lower values take precedence. Attribute value is subject to PTP network planning. Only applicable for BC with telecom profile configured for time synchronization according to G.8275.1.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: masterOnly
attribute.description:
Defines if port can only act as master or both master and slave for PtpBcOcPort MO, only applicable if configured according to G.8275.1.
If true, PtpBcOcPort MO can only act as master. If false, PtpBcOcPort MO can act both as master or slave.
Attribute value is subject to PTP network planning. Only applicable for GM and BC whit telecom profile configured for time synchronization according to G.8275.1.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: operationalState
attribute.description: The operational state.

attribute.name: pBit
attribute.description:
PCP value used for transmitted Ethernet frames when they are carried over VLAN.
If transportVlan is not set, this attribute is ignored.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: portDS
attribute.description: Port Data Set

attribute.name: ptpBcOcPortId
attribute.description: The value component of the RDN.

attribute.name: ptpMulticastAddress
attribute.description:
Multicast address.
If underlaying transport interface is not EthernetPort MO, this attribute is ignored.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: ptpPathTimeError
attribute.description:
Time error of PTP path at node interface.
Sum of boundary clock, transparent clock and asymmetry errors of worst case path from grandmaster to node. Error is theoretical static error of each component.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: ptpPortStatus
attribute.description: Status of PTP port.

attribute.name: syncMessageInterval
attribute.description:
Synchronization message transmission interval expressed as logarithm of time in seconds (base of 2).
Positive value indicates time in seconds between messages. Negative value indicates number of messages per second.
Example: If value is -4, 16 messages sent per second. If value is 2, message sent every 4 seconds.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: transportInterface
attribute.description:
References to underlying transport entity.
Can be MO type EthernetPort, AddressIPv4 or AddressIPv6.
attribute.dependencies: Must refer to EthernetPort MO, if attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is IEEE_1588_J3, or G_8275_1, or IEEE_1588_TIME_DEFAULT, or IEEE_1588_TIME_SLOW. Must refer to AddressIPv4 MO or AddressIPv6 MO, if attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is G_8265_1 or G_8275_2. All ports created on slave-only ordinary clocks with ptpProfile G_8265_1 or G_8275_2 must have unique combination of IP address, associatedGrandmaster and transportInterface.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.

attribute.name: transportVlan
attribute.description:
Reference to underlying encapsulation.
Can only refer to VlanPort MO.
Used when carrying PTP over VLAN. If attribute is not set, PTP is carried over untagged Ethernet.
attribute.dependencies: Must be NIL, if attribute ptpProfile in BoundaryOrdinaryClock MO is G_8265_1 or G_8275_2. Cannot refer to VlanPort MO when attribute isTagged in VlanPort MO is set to false. If two PtpBcOcPort MOs refer to same EthernetPort MO, then their transportVlan attributes must have different values. One of them can be NIL, but not both. If NIL, must refer to VlanPort MO, where - VlanPort::encapsulation refers to same EthernetPort MO as this attribute, or - VlanPort::encapsulation refers to LagPort MO, where one value in LagPort MO::encapsulation refers to same EthernetPort MO as this attribute.
attribute.disturbances: Changing this attribute can cause traffic disturbances.
